properties.name: Community Information
properties.webBody:
This Community Information is being issued for Athlone, Poowong North, Ripplebrook.

  • There are 2 fires in Swan Rd Athlone as a result of a storm cell and ensuing lightning strikes in the area.
  • Smoke may be visible from nearby roads and communities as firefighters extinguish the fires. 
There is no immediate threat to the community and no action is required.
This message was issued by Country Fire Authority.

Unless the situation changes, this will be the last message issued for this fire

Use multiple sources to stay informed: 
  • www.emergency.vic.gov.au.
  • VicEmergency Hotline - freecall 1800 226 226.
  • VicEmergency app.
  • Facebook or Twitter (#vicfires).
  • Tune in to ABC Local Radio, commercial and designated community radio stations, or Sky News TV.

Accessibility:
The following service can help you, or someone you know, access information during an emergency.
  • To access this information in other languages call the Translating and Interpreting Services on 131 450 (freecall) and ask them to call VicEmergency Hotline.
  • If you are deaf, hard of hearing, or have a speech/communication impairment contact National Relay Service on 1800 555 677 and ask them to call the VicEmergency Hotline.

There is currently no threat to you, but you should stay informed and monitor conditions.
What you should do:

properties.name: Watch & Act
properties.webBody:
This Watch and Act message is being issued for Glenmore, Ingliston, Rowsley.

  • There is a grassfire at Glenmore Rd, Glenmore that is not yet under control.
  • This grassfire is travelling slowly from Glenmore Road in a north-easterly direction towards Ingliston Road and Ironbark Road.
  • The fire has currently burnt 145 hectares.
  • Emergency service crews will continue to secure the perimeter of the fire overnight.
  • Aircraft is actively supporting ground crews due to the inaccessible terrain.
  • There is currently no imminent risk to communities and properties, though you should continue to monitor the conditions as the situation could change quickly.
  • Smoke will be visible from nearby communities.
  • This Watch and Act message replaces the Advice issued at 04.10pm. 
Staying close to a building where you can shelter is the safest option, as conditions can change suddenly.

Continue to stay informed and monitor conditions.
What you should do:
  • Monitor changes, including increased wind speed, change in wind direction, smoke or poor visibility that indicates the situation is changing. 
  • If you are away from home, do not return.
  • Enact your fire survival plan.

If the situation changes you will need to leave quickly. Plan to:
  • Take your pets, medications, mobile phone and charger.
  • Travel to the home of family or friends that are away from the warning area.
  • Emergency services may not be able to help you if you decide to stay.
Impacts in your area:

Road Closures:
  • Glenmore Road, 1km from the Ballan-Geelong Road.
  • Glenmore Road at Dog Trap Road.
  • Intersection of McCormacks Road and Ironbark Road.
  • Carpark into the Werribee Gorge off Ingliston Road near the railway line.
This message was issued by Country Fire Authority.

The next update is expected by 18/02/2023 09:00 am or as the situation changes.

Use multiple sources to stay informed:
  • www.emergency.vic.gov.au
  • VicEmergency Hotline - freecall 1800 226 226
  • VicEmergency app
  • Facebook or Twitter (#vicfires)
  • Tune in to ABC Local Radio, commercial and designated community radio stations, or Sky News TV.
Accessibility:
The following services can help you, or someone you know, access information during an emergency.
  • To access this information in other languages, call the Translating and Interpreting Service on 131 450 (freecall) and ask them to call VicEmergency Hotline.
  • If you are deaf, hard of hearing, or have a speech/communication impairment contact National Relay Service on 1800 555 677 and ask them to call the VicEmergency Hotline.
